SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Schedule C, Part II-A Explanation of Four Year Averaging
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Tuscarawas County YMCA pays dues to the Ohio Alliance of YMCA's who in turn conducts lobbying activities. 2014 was the first year that the Tuscarawas County YMCA was provided with a reportable amount of those expenses.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Schedule D, Part IV, Line 2b Custodial Accounts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The YMCA acts as custodian for funds of related groups and organizations. All transactions are approved by authorized group representatives with the funds being maintained in a separate bank account from YMCA operating funds.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Schedule D, Part V, Line 4 EXPLANATION: INTENDED USE OF ENDOWMENT FUNDS
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE YMCA AND THE FOUNDATION HAVE ADOPTED THE PROVISION UNDER THE UNIFORM PRUDENT MANAGEMENT INSTITUTIONAL FUNDS ACT (UPMIFA) AND HAS ADOPTED A SPENDING POLICY THAT SEEKS TO PRESERVE AND BUILD THE PERMAMENT FUNDS ENTRUSTED TO THE YMCA AND THE FOUNDATION ON A REAL DOLLAR BASIS AND TO MAINTAIN THE DISTRIBUTION LEVELS IN PERIODS OF DOWN MARKETS. INVESTMENT OBJECTIVES OF THE YMCA AND THE FOUNDATION ARE TO MANAGE THE PORTFOLIO IN A MANNER THAT WILL MAXIMIZE THE BENEFITS INTENDED BY THE DONORS; PROVIDE PERPETUAL FINANCIAL SUPPORT FOR THE YMCA AND THE FOUNDATION; AND ACHIEVE A TOTAL RETURN OVER TIME SUFFICIENT TO PRESERVE AND INCREASE THE PURCHASING POWER OF THE ASSETS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Schedule D, Part V, Line 4 Intended uses of endowment funds
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: To provide operations support to the Tuscarawas County YMCA from endowment earnings.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part III, Line 1 Supplementary information
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE TUSCARAWAS COUNTY YMCA IS A CHARITABLE, COMMUNITY SERVICE ORGANIZATION THAT INCLUDES MEN, WOMEN, AND CHILDREN OF ALL AGES, ABILITIES, INCOMES, RACES AND RELIGIONS. WE ARE DEDICATED TO BUILDING STRONG KIDS, STRONG FAMILIES, AND STRONG COMMUNITIES, BY PUTTING CHRISTIAN PRINCIPLES INTO PRACTICE THROUGH PROGRAMS THAT PROMOTE HEALTHY LIFESTYLES, STRONG VALUES, LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT, COMMUNITY INTERACTION, INTERNATIONAL UNDERSTANDING. ALL PERSONS ARE WELCOME AT THE YMCA, REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY. OUR YMCA IS FOUNDED AND LED BY VOLUNTEERS, FROM OUR COMMUNITY: VOLUNTEERS ALSO SERVE AS MENTORS, COACHES, PROGRAM LEADERS, INSTRUCTORS, AND MORE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 REVIEWED BY AUDIT COMMITTEE WITH OUTSIDE INDEPENDENT AUDITOR AND THEN REVIEWED BY BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c Conflict of interest policy
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The policy is distributed annually and each member must sign and return. Members abstain from voting in cases where a conflict exists.
